Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[There is a photo attached to this report of dead pigeons littering
the ground. Whatever they died of, it was not anthrax as small and
medium sized birds are resistant to infection with _Bacillus
anthracis_; their body temperature is too high to allow infection. On
the other hand dogs and cats would be infected if they had lapped up
the infected blood. But their deaths were very rapid. I suspect
someone had wittingly or unwittingly put out some poison. But it sure
made for good copy and heightening everyone's fears. This points up
the need for making sure that the journalists reporting on an event
are properly briefed.

For maps of Bangladesh, go to
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/middle_east_and_asia/bangladesh_rel96.jpg> and
<http://healthmap.org/r/00Sn>. - Mod.MHJ]
